`tests/` is the sole integration-level check on `ctx-summarize`'s runner contract — it validates end-to-end behavior against fakes and real subprocesses rather than unit-testing internals, so it's the place to look for how `runner::run`, `Fs`, and `Agent` are actually expected to interact.

The single file, `summarize.rs`, owns the fixture (`FakeFs::seeded()`) that other tests reuse, and pins the ordering contract (leaves before rollups, rollups propagating outward crates/foo → crates → root) along with the rule that rollup prompts must read prior stage output (intent.md + prior `.ctx`), never raw source. It also fixes error-variant behavior (`MissingPrompt`, `PathEscape`, `AccessDenied`, `Agent`) and the `MAX_TARGETS` scope-check boundary as externally-visible contract, not incidental detail — a change to any of these in the runner should be expected to break a specific assertion here.

`SubprocessAgent` tests require `sh`/`cat`/`true`/`exit` on PATH; this is an environment dependency, not a fake, and will fail silently-differently (not skip) on systems lacking them.

No intent.md exists for this directory.